### Core Modules

| Module | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `ui.py` | Streamlit web interface with configuration and visualization |
| `kg_extractor.py` | Dual-mode extraction engine (LLM + spaCy) |
| `kg_graph_builder.py` | Graph construction and visualization with NetworkX |
| `neo4j_handler.py` | Neo4j database integration and querying |

## üîß Configuration

### Extraction Modes

#### LLM Mode (Online)
- Pros: Higher accuracy, better semantic understanding
- Con*: Requires API key, internet connection, potential costs
- Best for: Complex text, academic papers, nuanced relationships

#### spaCy Mode (Offline)
- Pros: Fast, no API needed, privacy-preserving, free
- Cons: Lower accuracy on complex text
- Best for: Simple text, batch processing, air-gapped environments

### Neo4j Configuration

When Neo4j is enabled, you can:
- Store multiple named graphs
- Query entity relationships
- Find shortest paths between entities
- Perform graph analytics
- Export and import graph data

